data.text:
Group photograph signed by the first four cosmonauts.

Gherman Titov (Russian).

Andriyan Nikolayev (Russian).

Pavel Popovich (Russian).

Yuri Gagarin (Russian).

ca. 1962.

Photograph with original transmittal envelope.

Gagarin became the first human to travel in outer space on April 12, 1961, when his space capsule Vostok I completed an orbit of the Earth; Titov was the second person to orbit Earth, on August 6, 1961, aboard Vostok 2, and was the first to spend more than a day in space, among several other milestones; Nikolayev became the third Russian in space when he piloted Vostok 3, in 1962; and Popovich became the fourth cosmonaut in space, when he piloted Vostok 4 in a flight that coincided with that of Vostok 3, the first dual space flight.
